In a speech at the Munich Security Conference, LTG H.R. McMaster emphasized the importance of addressing common threats to international security. He highlighted three priority areas: ensuring non-proliferation of weapons of mass destruction, defeating jihadist terrorist organizations, and strengthening the international foundations for peace and prosperity. McMaster called for holding the Syrian regime accountable for its use of chemical weapons, pressuring North Korea to denuclearize, and addressing flaws in the Iran deal. He also emphasized the need to cooperate in countering terrorist organizations and to strengthen international institutions. McMaster stressed the importance of upholding sovereignty and protecting against aggression in cyberspace and other forms of subversion. He concluded by emphasizing the need to renew commitment to shared values and work together to overcome today's threats.